Help.AdminDesc:
**/msgdel [amount]** - Deletes the specified amount of messages in a channel
\* **amount** - The amount of messages to delete

**/reset_economy** - Resets the economy of the guild

**/roleassign [roles] {message} {modify}** - Create a message for self-assigning roles
\* **roles** - The roles separated by semicolons (i.e. role1;role2;...)
\* **message** - The contents of the message
\* **modify** - The ID of the message to modify

**/joinrole {role}** - Specify the role that new users of the guild automatically get
\* **role** - The name of the role

**/settings {language}** - Change the guild specific settings
\* **language** - The name of the language file, without the '.json' suffix
Help.BasicDesc:
**/help {subsection}** - Simple help command
\* **subsection** - The subsection of the help command

**/information {user}** - Information about the guild, user and commands
\* **user** - The user to get information of

**/thought** - Awakening thoughts

**/card {suit}** - Draw a card, guess the suit to win credits
\* **suit** - Guess the card suit

**/coin {count}** - Heads or tails?
\* **count** - How many times the coin is flipped

**/generate [type_] [prompt] {temperature} {image_scale} {engine}** - Generate text or images using OpenAI
\* **type_** - Whether you want to generate text or an image
\* **prompt** - The prompt from which you wish something to be generated
\* **temperature** - The creativity percentage (50 by default)
\* **image_scale** - The resolution of the image (1024x1024 by default)
\* **engine** - The model engine which generates the answer (gpt-3.5-turbo by default)

**/perfstat** - Displays performance statistics
Help.EconomyDesc:
**/register** - Create an account

**/unregister** - Delete your account

**/balance {user}** - Displays the user's current balance
\* **user** - The user whose account balance you wish to see

**/deposit [amount]** - Deposits the specified amount to the user's bank
\* **amount** - The amount of credits you wish to deposit to your account

**/withdraw [amount]** - Withdraws the specified amount from the user's bank
\* **amount** - The amount of credits you wish to withdraw from your account

**/beg** - Beg for a chance to gain credits

**/rob [user]** - Rob another user for a chance to gain credits
\* **user** - The user you wish to rob from

**/leaderboard {to}** - Displays the richest users in the guild
\* **to** - The end position of the leaderboard display
Help.GameDesc:
**/brawl {bet}** - Create a game of brawl
\* **bet** - The amount of credits you wish to bet on a game of brawl

**/blackjack {bet}** - Create a game of blackjack
\* **bet** - The amount of credits you wish to bet on a game of blackjack
Help.GeneralDesc:
__**Bracket significance**__
[] = Required field
{} = Optional field

**/help Basic** - Basic commands
**/help Music** - Music commands
**/help Admin** - Admin commands
**/help Game** - Game commands
**/help Economy** - Economy commands
Help.MusicDesc:
**/connect** - Invites the bot to the voice channel

**/disconnect {after_song}** - Removes the bot from the voice channel and clears the queue
\* **after_song** - Disconnects once current song has ended

**/play [query] {insert} {pre_shuffle} {ignore_live} {start_at}** - Adds and plays songs in the queue
\* **query** - The song that you want to play (SoundCloud/Spotify/YouTube URL, or query)
\* **insert** - Add the song to the given position in queue
\* **pre_shuffle** - Shuffle the songs of the playlist ahead of time
\* **ignore_live** - Attempts to ignore songs with '(live)' in their name
\* **start_at** - Sets the song to start from the given timestamp

**/view {from_} {to} {seek}** - Displays songs in queue, with the ability to seek them
\* **from_** - The start position of the queue display
\* **to** - The end position of the queue display
\* **seek** - Seek songs via given keywords

**/remove [from_] {to}** - Removes songs from the queue
\* **from_** - The start position of the queue removal, or positions separated by semicolons (i.e. pos1;pos2;...)
\* **to** - The end position of the queue removal

**/shuffle {from_} {to}** - Shuffles the queue
\* **from_** - The start position of the queue shuffle
\* **to** - The end position of the queue shuffle

**/move [from_] [to] {replace}** - Moves the song to the specified position in the queue
\* **from_** - The current position of the song in queue
\* **to** - The position in queue you wish to move the song to
\* **replace** - Replaces the song in the target position

**/clear {from_}** - Clears the queue
\* **from_** - The start position of the queue clear

**/skip {to}** - Skips to the next, or to the specified, song in the queue
\* **to** - The position in queue you wish to skip to

**/loop {mode}** - Loops either the song or the entire queue
\* **mode** - The loop mode you wish to use

**/pause** - Toggles pause for the current song

**/filter {mode} {intensity}** - Applies an audio filter over the songs
\* **mode** - The filter mode you wish to use
\* **intensity** - Set the filter intensity percentage (35 by default)

**/volume {level}** - Changes the music player volume
\* **level** - Set the volume level percentage (50 by default)

**/replay {insert}** - Replays the previous song from the queue
\* **insert** - Add the song to the given position in queue

**/seek [timestamp]** - Seek a certain part of the song via timestamp
\* **timestamp** - The timestamp to seek (i.e. hours:minutes:seconds)

**/lyrics {title}** - Get lyrics for the currently playing song
\* **title** - Get lyrics from the specified title instead
